strategy: Consider integrating a model-based reinforcement learning component into the training pipeline. Instead of relying solely on model-free approaches like PPO, incorporating a model-based element where the algorithm learns a dynamics model of the environment can enhance performance. By understanding and predicting the consequences of actions, the agent can make more informed decisions, potentially leading to improved exploration and exploitation balance. This hybrid approach can be implemented by using simulative models such as neural network-based dynamics predictors alongside the PPO algorithm to guide policy learning.
